name: The Captain's Boil
description: Buzzy, maritime-themed destination specializing in boil-in-a-bag Cajun- & Asian-inspired seafood.
address: The Captain's Boil, 1487 Robson St, Vancouver, BC V6G 1C1

featured_reviews.review_id:
Better location than other Captains boil we went to. Food was alright with good portion for sharing. Quick service I guess with the time we went there, a little early for dinner. Table at the booth we sat down has a huge hole in it, washroom was really dark and dirty with sauce splat on the headboard Liked our server as she is attentive. Couple of stars off because 1. We ordered a plain fries for the kids but we got a season one that's a little spicy for little kids. 2. It gave me an upset stomach after I ate here that never happened to any seafood places I've been to.
Might as well go to other boil places for better experience and atmosphere. Debating if I should give this place another try.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Went on a Wednesday night and it was very quiet. I had the prawn and mussels as my main, and it was very good. I also ordered a side of fried rice and it was very tasty. The standard sides are not that great but they seem to come with whatever you order.

The music being played was really sad country about heartbreak. Not sure what clientele they are playing it for on a Wednesday night.

featured_reviews.review_id: Indescribably dissatisfied. Their "1LB" of shrimp included the head, which is not included in photos or the description, and their shrimp is not clean. The black intestine was still in every single one of the shrimp when i de-headed them. Did not include gloves, so my hands were stained. Horrific experience. Will not be back, and will not recommend.

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text: We apologize for any disappointment you experienced during your recent visit. Please note that our 1LB shrimp includes heads, and we also offer a headless shrimp option. We appreciate your feedback regarding the black intestine and will address it with our team to ensure a better experience in the future.

featured_reviews.review_id: Went there with my family and we were impressed. Staff was friendly and food was good. We were seated right away and waitress helped us with the menu. She answered our questions and familiarized us with their menu and the way they cook.  We ordered Pirate's feast with a lobster. Food came in bags, one bag of mussels, one bag of clams and the lobster, We got paper bibs, gloves and scissors to use. It was messy but the food was very tasty and we enjoyed it.

featured_reviews.review_id: So I have to say that the food was great!! I ordered King Crab and my fiance had Lobster, but the only reason I had King Crab was because I asked before if I could have half a Lb ( 1 Lb was $89), and the waitress said yes, but at the end when the bill arrived, they charged me full! another waitress told me they don't serve half Lb and I said the other waitress said yes, then they talked between them and instead of apologizing or trying to find another solution, the first waitress said that yes they don't serve half, but why would she said yes in the first place? But anyways, we paid full but this "small" mistake was very expensive, just have better customer service! If she would have accepted her mistake and maybe even apologized we could've understand but acting like the way she did, was not ok.

featured_reviews.review_id:
This is one of the better locations. Service and food quality always good and consistent. Staff are very pleasant and accommodating. Always a go to seafood     place for us. Delicious sauce and fresh. Gets messy, but messy is fun and delicious 

They do give you gloves and apron to stay clean
